snippet.textDisplay: 1:04:20

A truly independent set of solutions would be a capsule-type spacecraft like Starliner or Dragon 2 and a shuttle-type spacecraft like Dream Chaser, or a completely new type of craft (both from different manufacturers). Unfortunately, some developers/manufacturers have better contacts with the Government and politics than others and those with the best links are not necessarily the most capable, dedicated, or legitimate. The Space Shuttles retired in 2011. Why did it take until late 2019 to do this test flight?? Perhaps the Centaur stage could insert Starliner into orbit to retain more maneuvering fuel onboard Starliner? Congratulations on reaching an orbit. Best of success with all future launches. Go Starliner, go Dragon, go Orion.
